<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: A guest noted this over on the forum: <p>
If you roll up a Ranger, once you get to the part where you pick a god, Eru is not an option. You can still do 'no god' and then convert later, of course. It's rather odd, though, and perhaps inconsistent, as Archers <em>can</em> pick Eru. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: Not a bug.  A check of the relevant game data shows that Rangers are not supposed to be able to pick Eru. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Not complaining, but... why??? (Inquiring mind wishes to know.) 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: That decision was made before my involvement.  I only started after ToME 2.1, the first ToME 2 version to work for me. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./FearofFours">FearofFours</a>: Presumably because Eru does not allow sharp weapons and rangers are often quite nifty with a sword? 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: That's all I could think of, myself... but arrows are pointy, too, and Eru will allow Archers to worship him. (Even though some boomerangs are blessed... go figure...) 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./FearofFours">FearofFours</a>: The way I see it is that arrows are piercing, not slashing/slicing. It comes down to blood loss: minimal loss with an arrow, more loss with a blade. And archers are not so good with a sword as rangers. As for the boomerangs, well some ancient traditional boomerangs have been found with sharp flints along the blades to act as a slicing weapon as well as a stunning one. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Hm, that all makes sense. I've never played a ranger, but this still interests me. I guess an Eru ranger would be a new character class, then....(?) 
</p>
<p>
<a class="nonexistent" href="./ElIott">ElIott</a>: Yeah and maybe I'm wrong, but can't swordmasters and axemasters worship Eru? 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: I just tried a quick rollup. Swordmasters are not offered Eru on character creation. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./FearofFours">FearofFours</a>: <a class="nonexistent" href="./ElIott">ElIott</a>, IIRC they are only allowed to worship Eru by 'converting' to him at a later date. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: That's true of rangers, too. 
</p>
<p>
However, any class that gets the "no god" option can convert to <em>any</em> god later on.... which pretty well obviates the whole point of preventing Eru worship in the first place. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./ZV">ZV</a>: Umm, no? Think of newbies - start with Eru swordmaster and have a bad time. Quite discouraging, isn't it? OTOH to convert you must make it to Lorien and you probably know what's it all about then. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: The enjoyment of the game comes first.  It doesn't matter that a determined player can wreck his game by converting a swordmaster to Eru.  It'd absurd to allow a swordmaster to start the game following Eru.   That's not fun and there's no good reason to allow it. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: I didn't realize that a Ranger was considered a Swordmaster... 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: Well, combining what Martin said above with the fact that the most famous ranger in Middle-earth wielded Anduril, it seems clear that Rangers are "meant" to be able to wield swords. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Hm, well, fair enough then. <img src="./wiki/starshine/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> And no, I would never want for a newbie to run into an Eru swordmaster combination. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./ErisDiscordia">ErisDiscordia</a></strong>: <a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: "&lt;/deliberate misquote&gt; It'd absurd to allow a swordmaster to ... follow... Eru.&lt;/deliberate misquote&gt; That's not fun and there's no good reason to allow it." 
</p>
<p>
<a class="external" href=".forum.t-o-m-e.net/viewtopic.php?t=5470"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">http://forum.t-o-m-e.net/viewtopic.php?t=5470</a>  
</p>
<p>
FOR GREAT JUSTICE! 
</p>
<p>
<img src="./wiki/starshine/img/smile.png" alt=":-)" height="15" width="15"> <img src="./wiki/starshine/img/smile.png" alt=":-)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: I think the point, Erik, is that while Ent Eru Swordmasters are <em>possible</em>, they should not be immediately available to the unsuspecting newbie, who would probably be extremely frustrated by such a combination. (I happen to have at least one Eru-worshipping sword-carrying characters, myself.) 
</p>
